<p>This tower could be seen from the parsonage garden. Altogether fifteen works showing the tower with the churchyard around it are known; they were done between December 1883 and May 1885. See exhib. cat. ’s-Hertogenbosch 1987 and De Brouwer 2000. This is probably <hi xmlns:xsi="http://www.w3.org/2001/XMLSchema-instance" rend="italics">The old church tower at Nuenen with a ploughman</hi> (<rs xmlns:xsi="http://www.w3.org/2001/XMLSchema-instance" type="artwork" ref="artwork.xml#ill_2453">F 34 / JH 459</rs>), cf. <ref xmlns:xsi="http://www.w3.org/2001/XMLSchema-instance" target="let440.xml#n-9">letter 440, n. 9.</ref></p>
                        </note>
                        
                    
